narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I further developed grammar, vocabulary, and cultural skills this course.

A lot of grammar, vocabulary and reading comprehension is learned and practiced. Also speaking Greek each class and having to use what we know to speak and if we don't know a word finding a way to say it regardless.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths are the teacher. She is amazing and most caring. The strengths are the quizzes because it really forces you to memorize the material well and learn the vocabulary. A weakness would be that I wish we could speak more in Greek to improve our verbal skils.
I love the fact that we are made to speak Greek all the time. Even if our conversation in class goes off topic, we are still speaking Greek so it is still a learning experience.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes I would! Greek is a beautiful language and I highly recommend you take it with one of the nicest, caring, and engaging professors. It is an experience!
I would highly recommend this course, and Maria makes it fun to learn.
